Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 2022-10-20
Last Updated: 2024-09-28
This Privacy Policy describes how Fitdrop ("we," "our," or "us") collects, uses, and shares personal information from users ("you" or "users") of the Fitdrop mobile application ("the App").
Information We Collect:
Account Information:
When you create an account on the App, we may collect your name, username, email address, profile picture, location / timezone data, and phone number.
User Content:
We collect the content you post, share, or upload on the App, including photos, videos, comments, and messages.
Usage Data:
We collect data about your interactions with the App, such as the content you view, the users you connect with, and your engagement activities.
How We Use Your Information:
We use the collected information to:
Provide and improve the App's features and services.
Personalize your experience on the App.
Connect you with other users based on your preferences.
Use your phone number to help you find friends who are already using the App.
Connect your user account and information to Stripe, our payment processor for any purchases made for the Fitdrop App on our website.
Data Storage:
Your data is stored on secure servers. We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access or disclosure.
Third-Party Providers:
We may use third-party service providers to assist in operating the App and providing its features. These providers may have access to your personal information but are obligated to use it only to provide services to us.
Services include:
Google Firebase https://firebase.google.com/
Amazon Web Services https://aws.amazon.com/
Stripe https://stripe.com/
Compliance with Privacy Laws:
We comply with all relevant privacy laws in the jurisdictions in which we operate, such as the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).
The company also complies with the following GDPR statements:
1. Lawfulness, fairness, and transparency: obey the law; only process personal data in a way that people would reasonably expect; always be open about your data protection practices.
2. Purpose limitation: you must normally only process personal data for the specific reason you collected it and nothing else.
3. Data minimization: don't process any more data than you need.
4. Accuracy: make sure that any personal data you hold is adequate and accurate.
5. Storage limitation: don't store personal data for longer than you need to.
​
6. Integrity and confidentiality: always process personal data securely.
Sharing of Your Information:
We may share your information with:
Other users as directed by your privacy settings.
Service providers who assist in operating the App and providing its features.
Law enforcement or legal authorities when required by applicable laws.
Advertising:
Our app may include advertising for third party products and services. We and our advertising partners collect and use information about you to improve advertising, targeting and measurement systems so that we can show you relevant third party ads in our games. Ad identifiers, cookies and similar technologies To provide our games, Websites and interest-based advertising, we use ad identifiers, cookies and similar technologies. This section describes our use of these technologies and how you can manage your preferences.
Ad identifiers, cookies and similar technologies are used by us to provide our Services to you and in order to collect data from your device. These technologies allow us and our third party advertising partners to: recognise you and your device; provide interest-based advertising to you; allow us to understand how you interact with our apps and websites (for example, where we use cookies such as the Google Analytics cookie on our Websites); and allow our payment processors to process your payment instructions (for example, in app purchases handled by Apple and Google).
How do ad identifiers, cookies and similar technologies work?
Ad identifiers are non-permanent, non-personal identifiers such as the Android advertising ID and/or Apple's ID for advertising (the ‘IDFA’), which are uniquely associated with your device. Similar technologies include tracking pixels within ads. These technologies allow companies (including marketers and advertisers) to recognise your device when you use websites and applications. Cookies are small text files that are stored by your browser on your desktop computer or mobile device. You can withdraw your consent to cookies by updating the settings within your browser.
Your Rights:
- You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal data from our records. You can contact us at hello@fitdrop.xyz titled “Personal Data Inquiry - (Your username)” to initiate this request.
- Additionally you may delete your account and all user data manually in our app by going to setting > Privacy & Security > Delete Account
Your Choices:
- You can control the information you share with other users through your privacy settings.
- You can edit or delete your posts and account information at any time.
- You may choose to opt-out of certain communications or promotional emails.
Security:
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access or disclosure. However, no data transmission over the internet is entirely secure. You use the App at your own risk.
Children's Privacy:
The App is not intended for children under the age of 13. As per our terms and conditions, we only allow users 13 or above to join our platform. Any user who creates an account or uses Fitdrop, confirms that they are over the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware that this is occurring, we will take actionable steps to remove the information, and rectify the situation.
Updates to This Privacy Policy:
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices. The effective date will be indicated at the beginning of the policy.
Contact Us:
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, including data deletion requests, please contact us at:
hello@fitdrop.xyz
titled “Privacy Policy Inquiry - (Overview of your question/concern).